1 4. A finding that the sexual offender has maintained a clean record means during the
2 period the sexual offender was required to register as a sexual offender, the offender:
3 a. Was not convicted of a felony offense;
4 b. Was not convicted of a sexual offense;
5 c. Successfully completed, without revocation, a period of supervised release,
6 probation, or parole; and
7 d. Has successfully completed any cour t - ordered sexual offender treatmen t
8 program and any other court-ordered treatment program, if any. This subdivision
9 applies to any sexual offender treatment program completed regardless of
10 whether the program was completed while the sexual offender was incarcerated,
11 released, on parole, or on probation.
12 SECTION 2. APPLICATION. This Act applies to a sexual offender who has complied with
13 the registration requirements under section 12.1-32-15 for at least seven years before the
14 effective date of this Act or who reaches seven years of compliance after the effective date of
15 this Act.
